"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/973395","Department for Transport","false","2018-10-15","<p>The A14 Cambridge to Huntingdon scheme is on budget and on target to open to traffic by 2020/21 as planned.</p><p> </p><p>Highways England have encountered some challenges with the archaeology work schedule, but they have been able to work flexibly to ensure there has not been an impact on the construction programme. Highways England confirm this will not have an impact on the overall scheme budget and will be able to publish final costs once the scheme has completed.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2018-10-15T14:50:55.493Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/973395/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/973395/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/973395/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-09-13","A14: Road Works","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 11 September 2018 to Question 169126 on A14: road works, what estimate he has made of the delay to work on that road as a result of the archaeological work; and what estimate he has made of the cost of that delay.","false","Biography information for Mr Jonathan Djanogly","Huntingdon","Mr Jonathan Djanogly","174644"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/973396","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-10-12","<p>Investment in productivity improvements should go hand in hand with improved environmental outcomes. We have published an Agriculture Bill that will allow farmers to continue providing a supply of healthy, home grown produce made to high environmental and animal welfare standards.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2018-10-12T09:38:13.34Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/973396/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/973396/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/973396/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-09-13","Agriculture","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what recent assessment his Department has made of the adequacy of the balance between sustainability and productivity in UK farming.","false","Biography information for Stephanie Peacock","Barnsley East","Stephanie Peacock","174831"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/973397","Department for Education","false","2018-10-11","<p>The Education and Skills Funding Agency wrote to all MPs in January shortly after Carillion went into liquidation, to inform them how many Carillion apprentices were living in their constituencies. At that time there were no apprentices enrolled by Carillion living or working in Barnsley or South Yorkshire.</p><p> </p>","Guildford","Anne Milton",,"2018-10-11T10:51:21.843Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/973397/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/973397/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/973397/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-09-13","Carillion: Apprentices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many former Carillion apprentices have been made redundant in (a) Barnsley and (b) South Yorkshire.","false","Biography information for Stephanie Peacock","Barnsley East","Stephanie Peacock","174832"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/973398","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-10-10","<p>Information on preventative health spend is not collected centrally.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-10-10T12:38:27.663Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/973398/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/973398/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/973398/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-09-13","Preventive Medicine","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what proportion of the NHS budget has been spent on prevention of ill health in (a) 2009-10 (b) 2014-2015 and (c) 2017-18.","false","Biography information for Tulip Siddiq","Hampstead and Kilburn","Tulip Siddiq","174797"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/973399","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-10-09","<p>The Ministry of Defence has two Armed Forces Career Centres in the North East of England, in Middlesbrough and Newcastle, and that number has remained consistent over the past five years.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2018-10-09T15:09:51.117Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/973399/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/973399/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/973399/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-09-13","Armed Forces: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many armed forces recruitment centres there were in the North East of England in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame Morris","174689"
