"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971552","Treasury","false","2018-09-11","<p>The Government publishes distributional analysis of the impact of fiscal policies across the UK income distribution.</p><p> </p><p>At Autumn Budget, the Scottish Government benefited from a £2bn boost to their budget. Once the Scotland Act 2016 is fully implemented, more than 50% of the Scottish Government’s funding will come from revenues raised in Scotland. It is for the Scottish Government to take decisions across areas of devolved responsibility, including their own fiscal policy.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2018-09-11T14:57:31.74Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971552/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971552/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971552/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-09-11","Fiscal Policy: Scotland","1","House of Commons","What assessment he has made of the effect of the Government’s fiscal policies on household budgets in Scotland.","false","Biography information for Gavin Newlands","Paisley and Renfrewshire North","Gavin Newlands","906794"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971553","Treasury","false","2018-09-11","<p>This Government recognises the value of co-operatives and other mutually owned businesses, which are worth more than £36 billion to our economy.</p><p> </p><p>Since 2010, the government has reduced the corporation tax rate from 28% to 19% today, which benefits all businesses, including co-operatives, supporting investment, jobs, and growth.</p><p> </p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2018-09-11T14:54:03.597Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971553/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971553/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971553/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-09-11","Co-operatives: Finance","1","House of Commons","What plans he has to increase fiscal support for the co-operative sector.","true","Biography information for Preet Kaur Gill","Birmingham, Edgbaston","Preet Kaur Gill","906797"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971554","Treasury","false","2018-09-11","The best way to drive economic growth is to raise productivity. Since 2010, this Government has provided over half a trillion pounds in capital investment, increased investment in skills, and reduced taxes for businesses. Lower taxes provide a strong incentive for businesses to invest in raising their productivity. Tax cuts include reductions to business rates worth over £10bn by 2023, freezing fuel duty for 8 years running, increasing R&amp;D tax credits, and cutting corporation tax.","Salisbury","John Glen",,"2018-09-11T16:10:51.883Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971554/answer","Biography information for John Glen","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971554/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971554/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-09-11","Economic Growth","1","House of Commons","What steps he is taking to support economic growth.","false","Biography information for Chris Green","Bolton West","Chris Green","906799"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971555","Treasury","false","2018-09-11","<p>Infrastructure investment is at the heart of our strategy to drive productivity growth across the country:</p><ul><li><p>Through the £1.4 billion that will be invested as part of the Greater Anglia Franchise, a new fleet of over 1000 vehicles will be delivered by September 2020.</p><p> </p></li><li><p>The South-East LEP has secured £590 million from the Local Growth Fund for schemes to boost growth and help deliver new housing.</p><p> </p></li><li><p>£100-250 million will be invested to widen the A12 to provide extra capacity between Chelmsford and Colchester.</p></li></ul>","Newark","Robert Jenrick",,"2018-09-11T14:59:50.127Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971555/answer","Biography information for Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971555/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971555/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-09-11","Infrastructure: Chelmsford","1","House of Commons","What steps he is taking to invest in infrastructure in the Chelmsford area.","false","Biography information for Vicky Ford","Chelmsford","Vicky Ford","906800"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971556","Treasury","false","2018-09-11","<p>The UK and the EU reached an agreement in principle, in December 2017, on the financial settlement for the UK’s withdrawal from the EU. This was set out in the Joint Report on progress during Phase 1 of the negotiations. These principles will become legally binding through a Withdrawal Agreement as set out in the Government’s White Paper on legislating for the Withdrawal Agreement, published in July this year.</p><p> </p><p>Post-exit, decisions on spending will be made based on domestic priorities, considering the economic environment, the fiscal position and the negotiated outcome.</p><p> </p>","Salisbury","John Glen",,"2018-09-11T16:17:09Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971556/answer","Biography information for John Glen","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971556/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971556/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-09-11","EU Budget","1","House of Commons","What steps he is taking to reduce the total net annual financial outflow from the UK to the EU; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Kelvin Hopkins","Luton North","Kelvin Hopkins","906801"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971557","Treasury","false","2018-09-11","Fintech contributes more than £6bn to the economy annually, employing 60,000 people across 1,600 companies.","Salisbury","John Glen",,"2018-09-11T16:12:34.873Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971557/answer","Biography information for John Glen","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971557/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971557/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-09-11","Financial Services: Technology","1","House of Commons","What assessment he has made of the potential contribution of FinTech to the economy.","false","Biography information for Paul Masterton","East Renfrewshire","Paul Masterton","906802"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971600","Department for Education","false","2018-10-09","<p>Two surveys by the Department, which include questions on happiness and satisfaction among secondary school pupils, are the second Longitudinal Study of Young People in England (LSYPE2) and the Pupil and Parent or Carers Omnibus survey.</p><p> </p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2018-10-09T15:34:34.81Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971600/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971600/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971600/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-09-11","Pupils: Health","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what information his Department holds on student (a) happiness and (b) satisfaction in secondary schools.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","173510"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971601","Department for Education","false","2018-10-09","<p>I am concerned about the increase in unconditional offers and any adverse impact they may be having on students’ A level grades. That is why I’m looking closely at the practice and have asked the regulator, the Office for Students (OfS), to review the practice, and in particular, to assess the impact it might be having on attainment. If negative impacts on students are highlighted through this review, I will expect the OfS to take robust action, in accordance with its powers set out in legislation.</p><p> </p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah","173512","2018-10-09T15:56:51.593Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971601/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971601/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971601/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-09-11","Universities: Admissions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what assessment he has made of the effect on A-Level grade attainment of the increase in the number of students receiving unconditional offers from universities; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","173511"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971602","Department for Education","false","2018-10-09","<p>I am concerned about the increase in unconditional offers and any adverse impact they may be having on students’ A level grades. That is why I’m looking closely at the practice and have asked the regulator, the Office for Students (OfS), to review the practice, and in particular, to assess the impact it might be having on attainment. If negative impacts on students are highlighted through this review, I will expect the OfS to take robust action, in accordance with its powers set out in legislation.</p><p> </p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah","173511","2018-10-09T15:56:51.673Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971602/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971602/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971602/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-09-11","Universities: Admissions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what discussions he has had with universities on the use of unconditional offers for undergraduate places.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","173512"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971603","Department for Exiting the European Union ","false","2018-10-09","<p>The Prime Minister has been clear that the United Kingdom will cease to be a member of the European Union on the 29th March 2019 and we will no longer have Members of the European Parliament.</p>","Daventry","Chris Heaton-Harris",,"2018-10-09T12:59:44.547Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971603/answer","Biography information for Chris Heaton-Harris","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971603/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971603/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union ","Exiting the European Union ","2018-09-11","European Parliament: Elections","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, whether he has held discussions with Cabinet colleagues and EU representatives on the holding of European parliamentary elections in the UK in 2019 in the event that the UK's withdrawal from the EU is delayed.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","173513"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971604","Home Office","false","2018-10-09","<p>We do not hold data to assess whether there is a correlation between the sale of natural cannabis oil and the number of thefts on the high street.</p><p>A CBD, or cannabidiol product, in its pure form is not controlled under the Misuse of Drugs Act 1971. However, a CBD product, which contains any trace of the psychoactive compounds that are found in cannabis, such as THC, is considered to be a controlled substance under the Misuse of Drugs Act 1971 and therefore unlawful to possess and supply unless it fits the criteria for an ‘exempt product’ under the Misuse of Drugs Regulations 2001.</p><p>Enforcement of illegal sales of drugs is an operational matter for the police but we expect them to enforce the law.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2018-10-09T15:30:25.53Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971604/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971604/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971604/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-09-11","Cannabis: Medical Treatments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what assessment he has made of whether there is a correlation between the unrestricted sale of natural cannabis oil in health stores and the number of thefts on the high street; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","173514"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971605","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-10-09","<p>We do not want or expect a no deal scenario. As a result of the significant progress made in negotiations, we remain confident we will agree a mutually advantageous deal with the European Union. We are not, however, complacent, and have plans in place in the event the United Kingdom leaves the EU with no deal. Our overall programme of work is comprehensive, thorough and continuously updated.</p><p> </p><p>We have been clear from the beginning of this process that we want EU nationals currently working in the National Health Service to stay after we leave the EU and we are working to safeguard their future, regardless of the outcome of the negotiations.</p><p> </p><p>The Department continues to monitor and analyse overall staffing levels across the NHS and, and we are working across Government to ensure there will continue to be sufficient staff to deliver the high quality services on which patients rely following the UK’s exit from the EU</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2018-10-09T10:42:52.687Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971605/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971605/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971605/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-09-11","NHS: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, whether his Department has made preparations for reduced staff levels in the NHS in the event that the UK leaves the EU with no deal.","false","Biography information for Kate Hollern","Blackburn","Kate Hollern","173583"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971606","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-09-17","<p>Many National Health Service organisations, including general practices, use automated telephone messages as a way of reminding patients about their upcoming appointments. This can provide improved access to care for patients in a way that makes best use of clinicians’ time while avoiding missed appointments and their associated costs. We would expect NHS organisations to respond to feedback to ensure they use automated messages as effectively as possible and if patients wish to opt out of such reminders, they may contact their local NHS provider to request this.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2018-09-17T11:22:07.29Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971606/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971606/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971606/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-09-11","NHS: Telephone Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, if he will take steps to minimise the use of automated telephone messages by (a) the NHS and (b) general practices.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame Morris","173562"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971607","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-10-09","<p>This information is not collected centrally.</p><p> </p><p>Health Education England operates a widening participation programme which aims to develop a healthcare workforce that can relate to and be representative of the communities it serves. The programme includes specific activity conducted through the Sutton Trust’s Pathways to Medicine Programme, that relates to widening access to medical careers for under-represented groups and people of disadvantage.</p><p> </p><p>As part of this, Health Education England has established a five-year partnership with the Sutton Trust, backed by investment of over £210,000 over the five years, to work with two universities, in supporting around 300 individuals from under-represented groups and disadvantaged backgrounds to enter medical training. There around 550 participants who have gone through or are going through the programme.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2018-10-09T11:06:50.587Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971607/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971607/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971607/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-09-11","Medicine: Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how much the NHS spends on (a) supporting and (b) promoting careers in medicine to young people from deprived communities.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame Morris","173563"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971609","Department for International Development","false","2018-09-17","<p>DFID does not hold estimates for the total number of think tanks located in each African country it operates in. DFID’s funding via the Think Tank Initiative (TTI) supports 18 think tanks in eight countries in Sub-Saharan Africa.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-09-17T16:23:44.873Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971609/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971609/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971609/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-09-11","Africa: Think Tanks","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what estimate her Department has made of the number of think tanks located in each African country it operates in.","false","Biography information for Preet Kaur Gill","Birmingham, Edgbaston","Preet Kaur Gill","173584"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971611","Department for International Development","false","2018-10-09","<p>The UK is currently in the planning phase of the textbook review. The review will enable us to identify if and where examples of incitement exist. We will take steps to address any concerns uncovered by the review as appropriate once it is complete.</p><p> </p><p>In my last meeting with the Palestinian Minister of Education in May I challenged him on the need to prepare their population for peaceful coexistence.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-10-09T15:45:22.607Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971611/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971611/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971611/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-09-11","Palestinians: Schools","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what representations her Department has made to the Palestinian Ministry of Education on removing examples of incitement from school textbooks during the review of the school curriculum in the Palestinian Territories.","true","Biography information for Joan Ryan","Enfield North","Joan Ryan","173495"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971612","Department for International Development","false","2018-09-18","<p>The Palestinian Authority (PA) has taken action to help address concerns raised. This has recently included piloting new textbooks, and confirming their commitment to engaging seriously with the findings of an independent review of the PA curriculum. I continue to press the Palestinian Authority on these issues.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-09-18T09:08:15.77Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971612/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971612/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971612/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-09-11","Palestinians: Television","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, pursuant to the Answer of 23 July 2018 to Question 165444 on Palestinians: Television, what information her Department holds on the steps that have been taken by the Palestinian Authority in response to the UK government's raising of the issue of incitement.","true","Biography information for Joan Ryan","Enfield North","Joan Ryan","173496"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971613","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-09-18","<p>We have published data on reoffending after release from individual prisons here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/676622/prison-youth-accomm-probation-data-tool-jan16-mar16.xlsx" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/676622/prison-youth-accomm-probation-data-tool-jan16-mar16.xlsx</a></p><p> </p><p>Due to data quality issues this data is only available until September 2015. Work is ongoing to improve the quality of this information, with the aim that we can resume publication of this in the future.</p><p> </p><p>Since our probation reforms in 2014-2015, while prison staff still have a key role to play, Community Rehabilitation Companies (CRCs) are now responsible for delivering pre-release support for offenders.</p><p> </p><p>We have announced our intention to amend CRC contracts to introduce an enhanced through the gate service so that providers do more to help offenders find accommodation and access to employment or benefits on release. On 27 July we published a consultation, ‘Strengthening Probation, Building Confidence,’ which outlines a number of proposals to stabilise and improve probation delivery</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2018-09-18T16:20:52.917Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971613/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971613/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971613/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-09-11","Reoffenders","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what the average reoffending rate was of offenders who served sentences in (a) public sector and (b) private sector prisons in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","173585"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971614","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-10-09","<p>We are absolutely committed to improving the overall Personal Independence Payment (PIP) claimant experience as this is what claimants rightly expect and deserve. The three waves of research that have been completed, and were published in the PIP Claimant Research – Final Report have provided valuable insights, alongside other sources, to make improvements to the PIP application process.</p><p> </p><p>Here are some of the key improvements we have made to the PIP application process:</p><ul><li>In April 2018 we increased our use of SMS text messages to better keep claimants updated about the progress of their claim</li><li>In April 2018 we launched a series of PIP videos to help claimants better navigate and understand the PIP claims process and the types of supporting evidence to send and;</li><li>In October 2016 (after the wave 1 fieldwork), we published a revised version of the PIP2 questionnaire where the language, style and tone of the form was simplified, and paragraphs were shortened to make it easier to understand and more focused for claimants to complete;</li></ul><p> </p><p>However, I recognise that there is more to do to improve the application process and that is why we will be commissioning independent research to support further improvements to the PIP2 questionnaire. In addition to the independent research, we are also progressing options to video record PIP face-to-face assessments to help increase people’s trust in the assessment process. We have been working over the summer to gather views from claimants, representative bodies and health professionals on video recording in order to inform a live testing pilot later in the year, which will inform wider rollout decisions.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2018-10-09T10:53:12.75Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971614/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971614/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971614/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-09-11","Personal Independence Payment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what steps her Department is taking in response to the findings of its report, Personal Independence Payment Claimant Research – Final Report, published in September 2018, to improve the application process for personal independence payment claimants.","false","Biography information for Kate Hollern","Blackburn","Kate Hollern","173586"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971616","Department for Exiting the European Union ","false","2018-10-09","<p>The Government has been clear on the outcome it wants to achieve, which is to secure a mutually advantageous deal with the EU. However, we have already carried out very significant ‘no deal’ preparations for the unlikely event that we reach March 2019 without agreeing a deal. We have successfully passed critical legislation, signed international agreements, recruited additional staff and guaranteed certain EU funding in a ‘no deal’ scenario.</p><p>We have already published a series of 77 technical notices so that businesses and citizens have time to prepare in the event of a 'no deal' scenario. These are available on gov.uk in a centralised location that is easy for people to access and use.</p><p> </p>","Daventry","Chris Heaton-Harris",,"2018-10-09T13:02:18.547Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971616/answer","Biography information for Chris Heaton-Harris","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971616/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971616/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union ","Exiting the European Union ","2018-09-11","Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, whether the Government plans to publish its contingency plans for no deal being reached on the UK leaving the EU.","false","Biography information for Kate Hollern","Blackburn","Kate Hollern","173587"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971617","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-09-18","<p>​The UK remains gravely concerned by proposals to demolish the Bedouin community of Khan al-Ahmar which the UN has said could amount to ‘forcible transfer’, in violation of International Humanitarian Law. Following the decision of the Israeli Supreme Court on 5 September, the Foreign and Commonwealth Office issued a statement with France, Germany, Spain and Italy, reiterating our call to the Israeli Government not to go ahead with its plan to demolish the village – including its school – and displace its residents. We will continue to raise concerns with the Israeli authorities as opportunities arise.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-09-18T13:38:11.13Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971617/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971617/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971617/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-09-11","Israel: Palestinians","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will make representations to the Government of Israel on its plans to demolish the village of Khan Al Mar.","false","Biography information for Kate Hollern","Blackburn","Kate Hollern","173588"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971618","Department for Exiting the European Union ","false","2018-10-18","<p>The government holds regular discussions with the EU on the future economic partnership, covering a wide range of topics. as minimising disruption for consumers is in the mutual interests of both sides. The government’s White Paper sets out proposals for the future relationship we want to build with the European Union, including new arrangements for services and digital sectors. The government published a technical notice on 13th September 2018 which provides guidance on mobile roaming in the unlikely event that we leave the EU without a deal.</p><p> </p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2018-10-18T13:57:31.95Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971618/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971618/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971618/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union ","Exiting the European Union ","2018-09-11","Mobile Phones: Fees and Charges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, whether the negotiations on the UK leaving the EU have included ensuring that mobile phone roaming charges will not be applied to British Citizens after the UK's departure from the EU.","false","Biography information for Hugh Gaffney","Coatbridge, Chryston and Bellshill","Hugh Gaffney","173589"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971619","Northern Ireland Office","false","2018-10-09","<p>The budget for the payment of salaries to MLAs is held by the Assembly Commission which is the corporate body of the NI Assembly. Any money that is unspent or savings realised throughout a year would be returned to the central Consolidated Fund for redistribution within the Northern Ireland Civil Service.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2018-10-09T10:24:55.64Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971619/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971619/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971619/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2018-09-11","Northern Ireland Assembly: Members","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, whether the savings accrued to the public purse as a result of the reduction in the pay of Members of the Legislative Assembly will be allocated to her Department.","false","Biography information for Ged Killen","Rutherglen and Hamilton West","Ged Killen","173590"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971620","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-09-17","<p>Guidance on fire safety, including patients with specific dependencies such as vulnerable adults and young children, is provided to National Health Service organisations in the Health Technical Memorandum 05 publications, generally referred to as Firecode. All Firecode guidance will be reviewed in the light of the recommendations of the Grenfell Inquiry.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2018-09-17T13:28:46.847Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971620/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971620/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971620/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-09-11","Fire Prevention: Hospitals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, whether he plans to bring forward legislative proposals to tackle the fire risk to (a) vulnerable adults and (b) young children in hospitals.","false","Biography information for Karen Lee","Lincoln","Karen Lee","173591"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971621","Home Office","false","2018-10-09","<p>A reply to the Hon. Member for East Dunbartonshire's letter of 19 April 2018, reference JS2981, was sent by post on 10 September 2018.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-10-09T16:09:33.927Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971621/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971621/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971621/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-09-11","Members: Correspondence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, when he plans to respond to the letter from the hon. Member for East Dunbartonshire of 19 April 2018, reference JS2981, on behalf of a constituent enquiry in relation to the Windrush Generation.","false","Biography information for Jo Swinson","East Dunbartonshire","Jo Swinson","173541"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971622","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-09-17","<p>An Impact Assessment was published on 19 July alongside the consultation on the closure the Feed-in Tariff scheme. Information provided through the consultation will be used to provide an updated Impact Assessment to accompany the Government response in due course.</p><p> </p><p>The Impact Assessment and consultation can be found at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/feed-in-tariffs-scheme" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/feed-in-tariffs-scheme</a>.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2018-09-17T15:21:50.417Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971622/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971622/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971622/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-09-11","Solar Power: Redundancy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what estimate he has been made of the cost to the public purse of redundancies as a result of proposals to close of the (a) feed-in and (b) export tariff for solar power.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","173592"
